resource.title: Treatment plan for pancreatic adenocarcinoma
resource.description: Comprehensive treatment plan including Surgery, Chemotherapy, Radiotherapy

resource.conclusion: Patient shows improving status for pancreatic adenocarcinoma. Naoki Abadi, a 54-year-old Asian male diagnosed with Stage IV pancreatic adenocarcinoma, underwent pancreatectomy followed by six cycles of chemotherapy and 15 radiation therapy sessions. He is currently in the follow-up phase post-treatment with improving clinical status. Comorbidities include hypertension and diabetes mellitus. Allergies to penicillin and codeine. Former smoker, no alcohol consumption, retired teacher with Medicare insurance.
